    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Restaurant",
          "arabic": "مطعم"
        },
        "text": "The word for 'restaurant' is \"مطعم\" (Maṭʿam). This is a common and essential word for finding food.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "وين المطعم؟",
            "english": "Where is the restaurant?",
            "transliteration": "Wēn il-maṭʿam?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "بدي مطعم أكل لبناني.",
            "english": "I want a Lebanese food restaurant.",
            "transliteration": "Biddī maṭʿam akil libnānī."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Cafe",
          "arabic": "قهوة / كافيه"
        },
        "text": "For 'cafe,' you can use \"قهوة\" (Qahwe) or \"كافيه\" (Kāfīh). \"قهوة\" literally means coffee but often refers to a cafe, especially traditional ones. \"كافيه\" is more modern.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "في قهوة قريبة؟",
            "english": "Is there a cafe nearby?",
            "transliteration": "Fī qahwe qarībe?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "بدي كافيه هادي.",
            "english": "I want a quiet cafe.",
            "transliteration": "Biddī kāfīh hādī."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Supermarket",
          "arabic": "سوبر ماركت"
        },
        "text": "'Supermarket' is usually \"سوبر ماركت\" (Sūbar Mārakit). For a smaller, local grocery store, you might hear \"دكانة\" (Dukkāne). We will focus on \"سوبر ماركت\".",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "وين السوبر ماركت؟",
            "english": "Where is the supermarket?",
            "transliteration": "Wēn is-sūbar mārakit?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "بدي أروح ع السوبر ماركت.",
            "english": "I want to go to the supermarket.",
            "transliteration": "Biddī arūḥ ʿas-sūbar mārakit."
          }
        ]
      }
