        "title": {
          "english": "Bus Stop",
          "arabic": "موقف باص"
        },
        "text": "The word for 'bus stop' is \"موقف باص\" (Mawqaf Bāṣ). \"موقف\" means stop or station.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "وين موقف الباص؟",
            "english": "Where is the bus stop?",
            "transliteration": "Wēn mawqaf il-bāṣ?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "بدي أروح على موقف الباص.",
            "english": "I want to go to the bus stop.",
            "transliteration": "Biddī arūḥ ʿala mawqaf il-bāṣ."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Taxi",
          "arabic": "تاكسي"
        },
        "text": "'Taxi' is \"تاكسي\" (Tāksī). You can also say \"سيارة أجرة\" (Sayyārit ujra) but \"تاكسي\" is much more common.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "بدي تاكسي للمطار.",
            "english": "I want a taxi to the airport.",
            "transliteration": "Biddī tāksī lil-maṭār."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "في تاكسي هون؟",
            "english": "Is there a taxi here?",
            "transliteration": "Fī tāksī hōn?"
