    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'How do I get to...?'",
          "arabic": "كيف بوصل لـ...؟"
        },
        "text": "To ask 'How do I get to...?' in Levantine, you say \"كيف بوصل لـ...؟\" (Kīf bōṣal la...?). This is essential for getting directions.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "كيف بوصل للمستشفى؟",
            "english": "How do I get to the hospital?",
            "transliteration": "Kīf bōṣal lil-mustashfa?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "كيف بوصل ع البنك؟",
            "english": "How do I get to the bank?",
            "transliteration": "Kīf bōṣal ʿal-bank?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'Is there...?'",
          "arabic": "في...؟"
        },
        "text": "To ask 'Is there...?' or 'Are there...?' in Levantine, you use \"في...؟\" (Fī...?). It's a very common way to inquire about the existence of something.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "في صيدلية قريبة؟",
            "english": "Is there a pharmacy nearby?",
            "transliteration": "Fī ṣaydaliyye qarībe?"
